      "FacilityID": 1000116682,
      "SummaryText": "This Executive Summary includes a brief summary of the following elements of the Risk Management Plan (RMP) prepared by Saguaro Power Company (with modeling assistance from Broadbent & Associates, Inc.) for their facility located at 435 Fourth Street in Henderson, Nevada:\n\n* Accidental Release Prevention and Emergency Response Plan\n* Stationary source and regulated substances\n* Worst-case scenarios and alternative release scenarios including administrative controls and mitigation measures\n* General accidental release prevention program and chemical-specific prevention steps\n* Five-year accident history\n* Emergency response Program\n* Planned changes to improve safety\n\n1.0  Accidental Release Prevention and Emergency Response Plan\n\nSaguaro Power Company has procedures in place to prevent, or minimize, accidental releases and to respond to emergencies, including:\n\n* Emergency response system \n* Ammonia handling procedures including off-loading and process equipment maintenance.\n* Employee training in handling, operation, and prevention of exposure\n* Contractors are required to perform all work in accordance with plant policies and OSHA PSM regulations\n* Lock out Tag out and hot work procedures\n* Incident investigation\n*  Procedures to ensure the mechanical integrity of the system\n\n2.0  Stationary Source and Regulated Substances\n\n* Saguaro produces electricity and steam.  In the process of producing electricity, anhydrous ammonia is used for selective catalytic reduction of Nitrogen Oxide emissions.\n\n3.0  Worst-Case Scenario\\Alternative Release Scenario\n\n* The Worst-Case Scenario assumes a 52,000 lb release at 5,200 lbs/min for 10 minutes with a toxic endpoint of 2.6 miles using the RMP COMP.\n\n* The Alternative Release Scenario assumes a 2,250 lb release at 445 lbs/min for 5 minutes with a toxic endpoint of 0.20 miles using the RMP COMP.\n\n4.0 General Accidental Release Prevention Program and Chemical-specific Prevention Steps\n\n* The Prevention Program at Saguaro Power C"
    },
    {
      "ESSeqNum": 1,
      "FacilityID": 1000116682,
      "SummaryText": "ompany (SPC) incorporates all elements of OSHA's Process Safety Management (PSM) program, as outlined in 29CFR1910.119. Within the program are the major components of process safety information, process hazard analysis, operating procedures, training, mechanical integrity, management of change, pre-startup safety review, compliance audits, hot work permits, clearance procedures, employee participation, contractor safety program, and an emergency response program\n\n5.0  Five-year Accident History\n\n* In the history of this facility, there have been no ammonia-related incidents resulting in the release of ammonia that has extended beyond the property boundaries of this facility\n\n6.0 Emergency Response Program\n\n* The facility has an emergency response program which includes the following elements: evacuation procedures, routes, and post-evacuation accounting of individuals; procedures for individuals remaining behind; emergency contact information; training; alarm system; site security, emergency medical treatment, emergency response procedures, PPE and emergency equipment, outside party coordination / public notification."
